<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\stdlib\mblen">mblen</sample>
    <title>mblen</title>
    <volume>C 运行库函数</volume>
    <routine_idx> slib_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>返回多字节字符的长度以确定其有效性。</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>int</return_val>
        <func_name>mblen</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>const char*</param_type>
                <param_name>mbstr</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>多字节字符字节序列的地址</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>size_t</param_type>
                <param_name>count</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>要检查的字节数</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>如果mbstr不为NULL，mblen就返回以字节为单位的多字节字符的长度。如果mbstr为NULL，或者mbstr指向一个宽结束符(L'\0')，mblen返回0。如果mbstr指向的对象在count指定字符范围内不能形成有效的多字节字符，mblen就返回-1。</para>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>如果mbstr是一个有效的多字节字符，mblen就返回以字节为单位的mbstr的长度。mblen检查mbstr中小于或等于count个字节的字符，但最多不超过MB_CUR_MAX个字节。</para>
    </remarks>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>mblen</routine_name>
            <headerfile>stdlib.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos </compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* mblen.cpp:this program use mblen to display the length of multibyte
 */

#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main()
{
    int     i;
    char    *pmbc = (char *)malloc(sizeof(char));


    i = mblen(pmbc, 0);
    printf(&quot;Length in bytes of multibyte character %x: %u\n&quot;, pmbc, i);
    free(pmbc);

    pmbc = NULL;
    i = mblen(pmbc, 1);
    printf(&quot;Length in bytes of NULL multibyte character %x: %u\n&quot;, pmbc, i);

    i = mblen(&quot;   aaaa&quot;, 1);
    printf(&quot;Length in bytes of multibyte character: %u\n&quot;, i);

    return 0;

}
</pre>
    </example>
<result>
Length in bytes of multibyte character 10540: 0
Length in bytes of NULL multibyte character 0: 0
Length in bytes of multibyte character: 1
</result>





